 provides a detailed analysis of confidenceestimator performance but does not address the loss of performance due tofalse negatives. We demonstrate that false negatives are a significant dangerin hard confidence schemes. Both papers restrict their discussion to confidenceestimators that produce strictly high- or low-confidence estimates (by settingthresholds), and do not consider soft confidence.ACM Transactions on Computer Systems, Vol. 21, No. 3, August 2003.336 ² S. Swanson et al.Wallace et al. [